<body>
    <h1>UX Standards</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"UXStandards-UXshouldercheck">UX shoulder check</h2>
<p>All developers are expected to reach out to the UX team for&nbsp;<strong=
>UX shoulder check</strong> before the Jira is marked as done. Please book =
a time with the relevant UX.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"UXStandards-Accessibilitytesting">Accessibility testing</h2>
<p>All developers are expected to&nbsp;do <strong>basic keyboard <span data=
-teams=3D"true">accessibility </span>testing</strong> <span data-teams=3D"t=
rue">(ie keyboard accessibility and zooming in/out), ideally <strong><u>bef=
ore</u></strong> the UX shoulder check.</span></p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/W1C+Accessibility+Requirements">W1C Accessibili=
ty Requirements</a></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Accessibility area</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Simple keyboard accessibility test=
ing</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Tabbing and focus</strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><spa=
n class=3D"UV3uM"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">1. All key user tas=
ks can be completed using keyboard alone.</span><br style=3D"text-align: le=
ft;"></span></span></p><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span cl=
ass=3D"UV3uM"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">2. Able to [Tab] into a=
nd out of all interactive elements.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176066619"><spa=
n>Users should be able to navigate through the application's user interface=
 by pressing the <strong>Tab</strong> key to move forward and <strong>Shift=
+Tab </strong>to move backward.</span>&nbsp;</span></span><br style=3D"text=
-align: left;"></span></span></li>
<li><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span>Ensure there are no "=
keyboard traps" where users can get stuck on an element and cannot navigate=
 away using the Tab key.</span><span class=3D"UV3uM">&nbsp;</span></span></=
p></li>
</ul><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">3. Able to close modals/popups and drop d=
own menus using [Esc].</span><br style=3D"text-align: left;"></span></span>=
</p><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">4. Keyboard focus is visible and you can s=
ee where you are on the page at all times.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176065836"><spa=
n>A visual indicator (e.g., a highlighted outline) should clearly show whic=
h element is currently focused, helping users understand their current posi=
tion.</span>&nbsp;</span></span><br style=3D"text-align: left;"></span></sp=
an></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,255);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,255);"=
 data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span data-huuid=
=3D"2977497382176065836">When a modal is displayed, the focus should move t=
o the modal.</span></span></span></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,255);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,255);"=
 data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span data-huuid=
=3D"2977497382176065836">When a new tab is opened or selected, the focus sh=
ould move to the new tab.</span></span></span></li>
</ul><p><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">5. Keyboard focus order is logical and ma=
tches the visual ordering of the page.</span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176064270"><span class=3D"UV3uM"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span data-huuid=3D"2977497382176066619"><spa=
n data-huuid=3D"2977497382176065053"><span>The tab order should follow a lo=
gical, predictable sequence, typically top-to-bottom and left-to-right for =
most interfaces.</span>&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span><strong style=3D"text-align: left;">Resizi=
ng the interface</strong></span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">1.</spa=
n><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"> All text on the page gets larger.<=
/span><br style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"=
>2. Content doesn't disappear, overlap or get cut off.</span><br style=3D"t=
ext-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">3. All buttons, for=
m fields, and other controls are usable.</span><br style=3D"text-align: lef=
t;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">4. Horizontal scrolling is not re=
quired to read sentences.</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"UXStandards-GEL">GEL</h2>
<p>We will use the following configuration as standard for Westpac One Core=
</p>
<p>GEL: Westpac Design Language</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://gel.westpacgroup.com.au/" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://gel.westpacgroup.com.au/</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Gel Next: Common library which provide reusable react UI components whic=
h implements above spec</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://gel-next-storybook.vercel.app/?path=3D/docs/component=
s-accordion--docs" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://gel-nex=
t-storybook.vercel.app/?path=3D/docs/components-accordion=E2=80=93docs</a><=
/p>
