<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>General spacing and size guidelines</str=
ong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>While the values specified here are pixel values, you should still use t=
he relative Tailwind classes which match the pixel values specified here. T=
hese values assume the user's font size is set to 100%. The Tailwind classe=
s will set the spacing to rem values that adjust with the user's font size =
setting.</p>
<p>Use the <a href=3D"https://gel.westpacgroup.com.au/design-system/wbc/fou=
ndation/layout/spacing" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">GEL's Spac=
ing table</a> to easily find the matching Tailwind class.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Font size</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Card tile: Use &lt;H1&gt; - <strong>30px</strong></li>
<li>Section name: Use &lt;H2&gt; - <strong>24px</strong></li>
<li>All labels: <strong>16px</strong>. Do not use a heading tag to format v=
alues</li>
<li>All hint text: <strong>14px</strong></li>
<li>All inline error: <strong>14px</strong></li>
<li>Value in all input field: <strong>14px</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Spacing</strong></p>
<p>All spacing is a multiple of 3.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>24px</strong> on all sides of the card</li>
<li>15px between the card title and the divider.</li>
<li><strong>12px </strong>between a field label, hint text, inline error an=
d input field</li>
<li><strong>6px</strong> between the input field and secondary information =
(eg 35 remaining)</li>
<li><strong>15px</strong> below each input field. This is GEL Next default.=
</li>
<li><s><strong>30px</strong> below each input field. This is GEL Next defau=
lt.</s></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Buttons</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Use the <strong>small</strong> size: Height =3D <strong>30px</strong></=
li>
<li><strong>9px </strong>between buttons</li>
</ul>
</div></td>
